divs: Sighting DetailsI walked to the beach and decided to take a picture of the ocean with my cell phone camera. Since the water looks more beautiful when viewed through my polarized sunglasses I decided to take two pictures. One through the lense of my sunglasses and one without. In the picture I took through the sunglasses you can see the blip in the background. The pictures were taken seconds apart. I didn't notice the blip until I reviewed the pictures on my computer when I got home.
Summary: Didn't see it until I reviewed pictures.
